A fast, scriptable CLI for Apple Notes (read/write + backups).

Usage: apple-notes [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

Commands:
  accounts  
  folders   
  notes     
  export    Export all notes to a folder structure on disk
  help      Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
      --account <ACCOUNT>
          Notes account to target (default: iCloud)
          
          [default: iCloud]

      --backend <BACKEND>
          Backend for reads (writes always use `osascript`)

          Possible values:
          - auto:      Auto-detect the fastest available backend (prefers DB when present)
          - osascript: Use `osascript` for all reads and writes
          - db:        Use the Apple Notes database for reads (macOS only); writes still use `osascript`
          
          [default: auto]

      --json
          Output JSON for machine consumption

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

  -V, --version
          Print version

Examples:
  apple-notes folders list
  apple-notes notes list --folder "Personal > Archive"
  apple-notes notes show x-coredata://... --markdown
  apple-notes notes create --folder "Personal > Archive" --title "Hello" --body "Hi!"
  apple-notes export --out ./notes-backup

